SPK_0: who are willing to be open to receive that power

100
00:06:09,250 --> 00:06:12,030
SPK_0: so they could win in a conflict with another class of people.

101
00:06:12,170 --> 00:06:15,830
SPK_0: And because the alliance between scientists and merchants

102
00:06:15,830 --> 00:06:18,210
SPK_1: by means of technology...

103
00:06:18,210 --> 00:06:18,810
SPK_1: Unholy alliance.

104
00:06:19,210 --> 00:06:20,350
SPK_0: Okay, unholy.

105
00:06:20,770 --> 00:06:22,990
SPK_0: Precisely against the church and the king, right?

106
00:06:23,810 --> 00:06:25,790
SPK_0: Achieved actual power success.

107
00:06:26,750 --> 00:06:28,470
SPK_0: Then we live in the aftermath of that world.

108
00:06:28,790 --> 00:06:32,290
SPK_0: And so if you would like to find a way to out-compete

109
00:06:32,290 --> 00:06:36,310
SPK_0: the adversary of those who control the current instantiation of that,

110
00:06:36,350 --> 00:06:38,210
SPK_0: whatever's going on with the relationship between

111
00:06:38,210 --> 00:06:40,050
SPK_0: political power and the academy,

112
00:06:40,270 --> 00:06:41,750
SPK_0: which I called the blue church later,

113
00:06:42,250 --> 00:06:44,690
SPK_0: you need to move to a place where there's a new...

114
00:06:44,690 --> 00:06:46,410
SPK_1: New power seed, effectively.

115
00:06:46,410 --> 00:06:47,770
SPK_0: A new seed of power, exactly.

116
00:06:48,050 --> 00:06:49,670
SPK_0: And the technologists of Silicon Valley

117
00:06:49,670 --> 00:06:52,670
SPK_0: are always looking for more gradients of power.

118
00:06:52,970 --> 00:06:54,650
SPK_0: And they will see the possibility.

